00:18:40,886 --> 00:18:43,150
He was a good man.

228
00:18:43,222 --> 00:18:46,316
[Sniffles]

229
00:18:49,828 --> 00:18:51,819
<i>[Man Laughing]</i>

230
00:19:09,982 --> 00:19:14,976
<i>Oh, I</i>
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

231
00:19:15,053 --> 00:19:18,648
<i>Gotta leave a little while</i>

232
00:19:18,724 --> 00:19:20,658
<i>Don't ask me why</i>

233
00:19:20,726 --> 00:19:24,457
Hello?
<i>And I</i>

234
00:19:24,530 --> 00:19:26,521
Hello.

235
00:19:27,633 --> 00:19:30,659
<i>I don't mean</i>
<i>to make you cry</i>

236
00:19:31,670 --> 00:19:34,537
George.
<i>My love</i>

237
00:19:34,606 --> 00:19:38,372
George, is this you?
<i>There's a light shining bright</i>

238
00:19:38,443 --> 00:19:41,776
<i>In my eyes tonight</i>
George?

239
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:45,681
<i>But I still see your face</i>
<i>through the night</i>

240
00:19:45,751 --> 00:19:48,242
Look, George, if this is you,
I don't want to talk to you.

241
00:19:50,122 --> 00:19:54,684
<i>I don't want to live without you</i>
George, is this you?

242
00:19:56,161 --> 00:20:01,098
<i>Oh, no, I won't walk away</i>
Where are you?

243
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:07,764
<i>I don't want to live without you</i>
You okay?

244
00:20:07,839 --> 00:20:10,933
George?
<i>No one</i>

245
00:20:11,009 --> 00:20:16,845
<i>Could ever take your place</i>

246
00:20:16,915 --> 00:20:21,545
<i>Well, "broski, '"this is</i>
<i>the nicest spot I could find you.</i>

247
00:20:23,322 --> 00:20:25,347
I don't believe
what happened.

248
00:20:28,794 --> 00:20:32,355
They, uh... They caught
the son of a bitch that killed you.

249
00:20:33,999 --> 00:20:35,990
Then they let him go.

250
00:20:38,003 --> 00:20:40,403
I have no idea
what to do about that.

251
00:20:45,911 --> 00:20:47,902
I don't think I, uh,

252
00:20:49,147 --> 00:20:51,513
ever really told you this
while you were alive, but...

253
00:20:55,020 --> 00:20:58,285
[Sighs]
I love you.

254
00:21:16,942 --> 00:21:19,035
Excuse me.
Mr. Kuffs?

255
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:21,102
They told me
I'd find you here.

256
00:21:21,179 --> 00:21:23,739
My name
is Sam Jones.
Hi.

257
00:21:23,815 --> 00:21:25,806
I know this might not
be the right time...

258
00:21:25,884 --> 00:21:27,875
and please don't think
badly of me...

259
00:21:27,953 --> 00:21:30,421
but I understand your brother
left you his district.

260
00:21:30,489 --> 00:21:33,083
Yeah, he did.

261
00:21:33,158 --> 00:21:36,093
I want you to consider
selling it to me.

262
00:21:38,597 --> 00:21:40,861
Since you're not in the field
of law enforcement,

263
00:21:40,932 --> 00:21:44,231
this could be
a great opportunity
for both of us...

264
00:21:44,303 --> 00:21:47,204
you to make some money,
and me,

265
00:21:47,272 --> 00:21:49,763
I get to put a good, strong man
in your brother's position.

266
00:21:51,710 --> 00:21:53,871
I'll give you
$100,000 now...

267
00:21:53,945 --> 00:21:56,914
and $1,000 a month
for the next two years.

268
00:21:58,350 --> 00:22:00,341
That's it. That's my spiel.

269
00:22:03,588 --> 00:22:07,888
Yeah, that, uh,
sounds wonderful,

270
00:22:07,959 --> 00:22:10,359
but could you give me
some time to think it over?

271
00:22:11,763 --> 00:22:13,788
I wouldn't expect anything less.

272
00:22:13,865 --> 00:22:16,333
Here's my card.

273
00:22:16,401 --> 00:22:18,767
It has my home number
on there. Call me anytime.

274
00:22:18,837 --> 00:22:21,101
I'll be expecting your call.

275
00:22:21,173 --> 00:22:23,607
Sorry about your brother.
Have a nice day.

276
00:22:28,847 --> 00:22:31,441
[Singing, Indistinct]
<i>[Coins Rattle]</i>

277
00:22:31,516 --> 00:22:34,144
You sure have to make
serious choices in life, don't you?

278
00:22:36,121 --> 00:22:38,112
<i>[Phone Rings]</i>
Patrol Special.

279
00:22:38,190 --> 00:22:40,420
<i>[Bell Jingles]</i>
Hey, Harriet.

280
00:22:43,862 --> 00:22:46,660
Nikki, Mr. Brown
is on line two.

281
00:22:46,732 --> 00:22:49,394
I'm busy.
Not bad.

282
00:22:49,468 --> 00:22:51,459
<i>[Nikki]</i>
<i>You're three weeks</i>
<i>late again, Mr. Brown.</i>

283
00:22:51,536 --> 00:22:53,629
<i>[Toilet Flushing]</i>

284
00:22:53,705 --> 00:22:56,902
Hiya, kid. Just the man
I wanted to see.

285
00:22:56,975 --> 00:22:59,944
Can I buy you
a free cup of coffee?
Show me the way, Bill.

286
00:23:00,011 --> 00:23:02,980
I'm not quite sure exactly
what's going on here.
[Continues, Indistinct]

287
00:23:03,048 --> 00:23:06,245
We should start talking
about how much you want
for the business.

288
00:23:06,318 --> 00:23:08,309
I have a little saved up.

289
00:23:08,387 --> 00:23:11,288
I can get some from...
my mother.

290
00:23:11,356 --> 00:23:14,018
I'm sure the bank
would lend me the rest.

291
00:23:14,092 --> 00:23:18,153
Well, uh, that's very nice
of you, Bill, but, uh,

292
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:20,926
believe it or not, I've decided
to take the job myself.

293
00:23:20,999 --> 00:23:24,526
Come again?
I'm gonna be your boss, Bill.

294
00:23:24,603 --> 00:23:27,333
- You're gonna what, kid?
- [Sighs]

295
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:31,470
He's a kid. Even if he
becomes a patrol special,

296
00:23:31,543 --> 00:23:33,534
he doesn't have the experience
to run a district.

297
00:23:33,612 --> 00:23:36,137
I do not want to hear "kid"
from this guy ever again.
I am not a kid!

298
00:23:36,214 --> 00:23:38,205
Calm down.
Kid, kid, kid.

299
00:23:38,283 --> 00:23:40,274
Would you tell him
that, please?
He's not a kid.

300
00:23:40,352 --> 00:23:44,015
Brad said I could go to
the academy during the day and
patrol with somebody at night.

301
00:23:44,089 --> 00:23:46,819
That's what I'm gonna do.
I spoke to the lawyer
from the D.A.'s office.

302
00:23:46,892 --> 00:23:49,122
He said the district's mine.
I'm taking it.

303
00:23:49,194 --> 00:23:52,129
Has he ever been convicted
of a felony? I'll bet he has.

304
00:23:52,197 --> 00:23:56,361
Shut up, Bill!
Have you?
No.

305
00:23:56,435 --> 00:23:59,700
Did you graduate
high school?
Yes.

306
00:23:59,771 --> 00:24:02,365
You have to go through
the academy.
I know, I know.

307
00:24:02,441 --> 00:24:06,707
He's gonna have to get
his hair cut, put on a uniform
and get rid of that attitude!

308
00:24:06,778 --> 00:24:09,611
I'm only gonna stick
around until I clean up
the neighborhood.

309
00:24:09,681 --> 00:24:12,741
Look, Kuffs...
That's the least
I can do for my brother.

310
00:24:12,818 --> 00:24:16,914
Oh, God damn it.
Why me? L...

311
00:24:16,988 --> 00:24:20,856
Bill, this is his district.
There's nothing I can do
about that.

312
00:24:20,926 --> 00:24:24,054
You think you've won?
Think again!

313
00:24:26,965 --> 00:24:30,093
Look, I understand
how you feel.

314
00:24:30,168 --> 00:24:33,399
Will you understand that
I don't want you here either?

315
00:24:33,472 --> 00:24:35,463
I heard about
Sam Jones's offer.

316
00:24:35,540 --> 00:24:39,442
If you don't want
to sell to Bill, fine.
Take that. It's a great offer.

317
00:24:39,511 --> 00:24:41,502
You don't know
what you're getting into.

318
00:24:41,580 --> 00:24:45,380
Captain, trust me.
L... I can handle this.

319
00:24:45,450 --> 00:24:49,113
Sure, and I just heard
turds can fly.

320
00:24:50,322 --> 00:24:52,313
Hear me.

321
00:24:52,390 --> 00:24:54,654
The first time you screw up
in any way...

322
00:24:54,726 --> 00:24:57,160
or if I catch you
going after Kane,

323
00:24:57,229 --> 00:24:59,220
you're out of business.
<i>[Bailiff]</i>
<i>Court is now in session.</i>

324
00:25:03,235 --> 00:25:06,671
Well, it's good to know
I have a loyal support team.

325
00:25:06,738 --> 00:25:10,640
What he doesn't realize is
the first time I screw up,
I'll probably be dead.

326
00:25:16,181 --> 00:25:19,173
<i>[Ringing]</i>

327
00:25:20,886 --> 00:25:23,150
Oh, God!

328
00:25:24,489 --> 00:25:28,789
Thank God
this is only temporary.

329
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:33,763
Imagine getting up
at 5:00 in the morning
for the rest of your life?

330
00:25:33,832 --> 00:25:36,130
It's worse than
nine-to-five.

331
00:25:39,504 --> 00:25:41,529
At least I still have you.
[Chuckles]

332
00:25:43,241 --> 00:25:47,177
Old Reliable. Oh!

333
00:25:47,245 --> 00:25:51,011
This is only part of it.
Wait until you see the uniform.

334
00:25:51,082 --> 00:25:53,642
It's beautiful.

335
00:25:54,719 --> 00:25:56,846
Well, what do
you think, huh?

336
00:25:58,390 --> 00:26:00,551
Even comes with a, uh,
matching hat.

337
00:26:03,562 --> 00:26:05,826
Feel like a dork.

338
00:26:05,897 --> 00:26:08,161
Let's go!

339
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:10,724
Come on!

340
00:26:10,802 --> 00:26:15,603
Come on!
Sir.
[Panting]

341
00:26:15,674 --> 00:26:18,666
Why are we doing
so much running? Aren't we
all going to be in cars?

342
00:26:18,743 --> 00:26:21,337
Move it, asshole!
Move it!

343
00:26:21,413 --> 00:26:24,211
Move it! Move it!

344
00:26:24,282 --> 00:26:26,842
This might have been
a terrible mistake.

345
00:26:29,220 --> 00:26:31,211
Can I help you?
Yeah.

346
00:26:31,289 --> 00:26:34,554
I'm looking for a really big gun
that holds a lot of bullets.

347
00:26:34,626 --> 00:26:36,457
God bless you, young man.

348
00:26:38,363 --> 00:26:40,524
I always wanted a gun.
<i>Is this what</i>
<i>you had in mind?</i>

349
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:44,291
It's a 9-millimeter
Beretta.

350
00:26:44,369 --> 00:26:46,963
Fifteen in the clip,
one in the pipe.

351
00:26:47,038 --> 00:26:49,506
Is there one that holds more?
No.

352
00:26:52,477 --> 00:26:53,739
I'll take two.

353
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:57,310
<i>[Man, Indistinct</i>
<i>Under Gunfire]</i>

354
00:27:00,385 --> 00:27:03,047
You probably won't hit anything.
That's what I'm here for.

355
00:27:03,121 --> 00:27:05,112
All right.

356
00:27:10,261 --> 00:27:13,253
<i>[Gunshots In Rapid Fire]</i>

357
00:27:23,808 --> 00:27:26,208
Where'd you learn
to shoot like that?

358
00:27:26,277 --> 00:27:28,268
Never shot a gun
before in my life.

359
00:27:28,346 --> 00:27:30,314
You're a natural, kid.

360
00:27:30,382 --> 00:27:33,510
Really? Is there such a thing
as being a natural at shooting?

361
00:27:33,585 --> 00:27:36,110
You betcha.
You mean I have talent?

362
00:27:36,187 --> 00:27:39,588
At shooting. Let's see
if you can do that again.

363
00:27:39,658 --> 00:27:41,455
Let me have
another target.

364
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:45,628
<i>At the start of your shift,</i>
<i>you report here and</i>
<i>you sign the log book.</i>

365
00:27:45,697 --> 00:27:49,565
Right.
At the end of your shift, you
come back and you sign out...

366
00:27:49,634 --> 00:27:51,625
if you don't get killed.

367
00:27:51,703 --> 00:27:55,400
Hey, Nikki, did you happen
to get that address on Kane
I asked for?

368
00:27:55,473 --> 00:27:57,464
Oh, yeah. Here.
It was in the book.

369
00:27:57,542 --> 00:28:01,273
Eh! Killer in the phone book...
never would've thought of that.

370
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:04,645
I don't know if you should
go gunning for Kane
on your first night.

371
00:28:04,716 --> 00:28:09,380
I'm not gunning for him.
I'm just gonna swing by
and see what he's up to.

372
00:28:09,454 --> 00:28:11,547
It's out of our district, George.

373
00:28:11,623 --> 00:28:14,114
It's all right. I can afford
the gas. What's next?

374
00:28:14,192 --> 00:28:17,320
Okay. You read
the reports of the day.

375
00:28:17,395 --> 00:28:20,887
Then you check the Teletype,
then the reports of incidents.

376
00:28:20,965 --> 00:28:22,956
Any ques...
Kuffs!

377
00:28:23,034 --> 00:28:27,095
This is Ted Bukovsky. He'll
be riding around with you
the next couple weeks.

378
00:28:29,774 --> 00:28:32,140
<i>Nikki, you can go home.</i>

379
00:28:34,212 --> 00:28:36,203
Wait one minute,
Nikki.

380
00:28:38,049 --> 00:28:40,609
Captain?

381
00:28:40,685 --> 00:28:42,676
May I talk to you
for a moment?
Sure.

382
00:28:42,754 --> 00:28:45,985
Listen, you're
really undermining
my confidence here...

383
00:28:46,057 --> 00:28:49,618
right in front
of one of my employees.

384
00:28:49,694 --> 00:28:52,663
How the hell do you
expect me to develop
leadership abilities...

385
00:28:52,731 --> 00:28:57,065
and learn how to make
decisions on my own if I have
a chaperone like Ted around?

386
00:28:57,135 --> 00:28:59,797
Who gives a shit?
Oh.

387
00:29:01,339 --> 00:29:03,671
Well, I can't afford him.
I went through the books
last night.

388
00:29:03,742 --> 00:29:06,609
My brother was living
month to month.
I'm almost broke here.

389
00:29:06,678 --> 00:29:09,909
No. I went through the books too.
You <i>are</i> broke.

390
00:29:09,981 --> 00:29:12,711
A lot of people dropped the service
when you took over.

391
00:29:12,784 --> 00:29:15,582
You got a week and a half,
two weeks tops. Then you're gone.

392
00:29:15,653 --> 00:29:18,588
You're history, and no lawyer
in the world can help you.

393
00:29:18,656 --> 00:29:21,819
Ted is here to keep you out
of trouble while you're among us.

394
00:29:30,802 --> 00:29:32,793
[Sighs]

395
00:29:32,871 --> 00:29:35,999
You must have messed up
pretty bad to deserve me, huh, Ted?

396
00:29:37,375 --> 00:29:39,843
[Scoffs]

397
00:29:39,911 --> 00:29:41,902
Look, kid.

398
00:29:43,581 --> 00:29:46,106
I'm a cop, okay?

399
00:29:46,184 --> 00:29:49,176
Personally, I think you patrol
specials are door-rattling jokes.

400
00:29:49,254 --> 00:29:51,313
Now, we can talk,

401
00:29:51,389 --> 00:29:54,586
we can tell each other lies,
we might even become friends.

402
00:29:56,294 --> 00:29:59,457
But in the next two weeks, if you do
anything that makes me look bad,

403
00:29:59,531 --> 00:30:02,364
I'll break you in half, okay?

404
00:30:03,968 --> 00:30:06,596
You get laid much, Ted?

405
00:30:08,439 --> 00:30:10,771
What do you mean?

406
00:30:12,410 --> 00:30:15,902
What do I mean?
[Chuckles]

407
00:30:17,982 --> 00:30:21,884
Uh, Ted, before we go,
I gotta run to the "toidey."
I'll meet you back here.

408
00:30:21,953 --> 00:30:24,945
You...
"Toidey"?

409
00:30:25,023 --> 00:30:29,483
Well, I'm sure Ted is the victim
of an unhappy childhood,

410
00:30:29,561 --> 00:30:33,327
and, some day, some psychiatrist
could release the caring human
that's struggling to get out.

411
00:30:33,398 --> 00:30:35,923
But right now,
I don't have the time.

412
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:38,867
Could you please tell me where
the Narcotics Division is?

413
00:30:38,937 --> 00:30:40,871
Thank you.

414
00:30:42,407 --> 00:30:44,432
<i>[George]</i>
<i>All right, all right, Doug.</i>
<i>I'll be honest with you.</i>

415
00:30:44,509 --> 00:30:48,639
Ever since my brother passed away,
I'm having a bit of trouble sleeping.

416
00:30:49,714 --> 00:30:51,477
Mm-hmm.

417
00:30:54,319 --> 00:30:57,049
Doug said half of one of these
would make you sleep...

418
00:30:57,121 --> 00:30:59,612
like you had a tit
in your mouth for eight hours.

419
00:31:01,259 --> 00:31:04,456
I don't know.
Ted's a pretty big guy, isn't he?

420
00:31:05,997 --> 00:31:08,966
Should I? Yeah, sure.

421
00:31:12,470 --> 00:31:15,030
Better to be safe.

422
00:31:15,106 --> 00:31:17,097
Stir it up.

423
00:31:24,582 --> 00:31:26,516
Oop.

424
00:31:26,584 --> 00:31:29,815
I'm real sorry about what I said.
I got you a cup of coffee.

425
00:31:29,888 --> 00:31:31,947
Next time,
shit before you sign in.

426
00:31:33,391 --> 00:31:36,792
Shit! Sign in!
In the car!

427
00:31:36,861 --> 00:31:41,389
Am I gonna be tested
on this later?
Maybe.

428
00:31:53,778 --> 00:31:55,507
You're not drinking your coffee.

429
00:31:55,580 --> 00:31:58,310
I don't like hot coffee.
I like cold coffee.

430
00:32:00,118 --> 00:32:04,179
Turn right at the next street.
You have some customers
at the end of the block.

431
00:32:16,067 --> 00:32:19,230
[Whistling]
[Yawning]

432
00:32:37,889 --> 00:32:39,754
That's the guy
that shot my brother.

433
00:32:39,824 --> 00:32:41,689
<i>[Ted]</i>
<i>Stop.! Stop.!</i>

434
00:32:41,759 --> 00:32:43,886
<i>[Horn Honking]</i>

435
00:32:43,962 --> 00:32:47,898
Look out!
Turn! Turn!

436
00:32:47,966 --> 00:32:50,764
Turn! Turn!

437
00:32:50,835 --> 00:32:53,030
- Stop the car!
- We're gonna lose him!

438
00:32:53,104 --> 00:32:56,073
Are you crazy?
Stop the car!

439
00:32:57,775 --> 00:33:00,642
Are you [Beep]
Trying to kill me?
What are you so angry about?

440
00:33:00,712 --> 00:33:04,239
I wanted to follow the guy.
Did you see a [Buzzer] crime
being committed?

441
00:33:04,315 --> 00:33:06,510
Did you see a [Distorted Note]
Crime being committed?

442
00:33:06,584 --> 00:33:09,018
If we follow him, we will
see a [Buzzer] crime
being committed.

443
00:33:09,087 --> 00:33:12,750
You are a [Electronic Note]
Patrol special. You don't go
looking for a [Buzzer] crime!

444
00:33:12,824 --> 00:33:15,793
If you see a [Distorted Note]
Crime being committed,
then you take action.

445
00:33:15,860 --> 00:33:18,693
Otherwise, your
[Distorted Note] job
is to service those people...

446
00:33:18,763 --> 00:33:21,527
who are stupid enough
to hire you to protect them.

447
00:33:21,599 --> 00:33:24,363
And if I'm gonna get killed
on this job, it's gonna be
by a [Electronic Note] bullet,

448
00:33:24,435 --> 00:33:26,699
not by
a [Electronic Note] bus!

449
00:33:26,771 --> 00:33:31,231
Now turn this [Distorted Note]
Car around and let's get back on
your [Distorted Note] patrol!

450
00:33:33,211 --> 00:33:36,146
You have a limited
vocabulary, Ted.

451
00:33:37,148 --> 00:33:39,139
