brother was good, but you shit!
Calm down, sir.

465
00:34:36,674 --> 00:34:38,665
Calm down.
We'll be right back.
Thank you, Mr. Chang.

466
00:34:38,743 --> 00:34:42,907
Get out of my store!
Ted, I told you. Four guys
in a green station wagon.

467
00:34:42,980 --> 00:34:45,073
You owe me
a billion dollars.
Where you going?

468
00:34:45,149 --> 00:34:47,879
I'm gonna go get Kane.
I can't let you do that.

469
00:34:47,952 --> 00:34:51,581
Well, try and stop me.
[Groans]

470
00:34:51,656 --> 00:34:54,557
Now calm down. We're gonna
take this guy's statement
and write up a report.

471
00:34:54,625 --> 00:34:56,957
You leave me
no choice, Ted.

472
00:34:57,028 --> 00:35:00,828
I'm gonna have to hurt you.
That's it.
Oh, man.

473
00:35:02,633 --> 00:35:06,125
Don't you see that getting Kane
would be as good for you
as it would for me?

474
00:35:10,708 --> 00:35:12,972
[Groaning]
I guess you don't.

475
00:35:34,899 --> 00:35:37,663
- You're pretty good at this.
- Thank you.

476
00:35:46,210 --> 00:35:48,804
Do you give up?

477
00:35:48,880 --> 00:35:51,178
Look, you don't have
to come with me.

478
00:35:51,249 --> 00:35:53,717
Just say I ditched you.
I'll give you money for a cab.

479
00:35:53,784 --> 00:35:56,048
I can't.

480
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:58,213
<i>[Siren Wails]</i>
Shit.

481
00:36:01,192 --> 00:36:05,856
<i>- [Car Door Slams]</i>
- What the hell is going on
around here, Bukovsky?

482
00:36:05,930 --> 00:36:10,629
[Panting]
Just investigating an armed
robbery. Same as you, Sergeant.

483
00:36:10,701 --> 00:36:15,229
- Is he a suspect?
- No. We were just...

484
00:36:15,306 --> 00:36:18,070
trying to decide who's
gonna write up the report.

485
00:36:18,142 --> 00:36:21,703
Don't try and
dick me around, Bukovsky.
You're already on probation.

486
00:36:21,779 --> 00:36:24,942
<i>I'll run your ass in for</i>
<i>assaulting another officer.</i>

487
00:36:25,016 --> 00:36:27,780
Now, did he start
the fight?

488
00:36:27,852 --> 00:36:29,877
Officer Bukovsky was, uh,

489
00:36:29,954 --> 00:36:31,945
just being kind enough to
show me some moves I missed...

490
00:36:32,023 --> 00:36:35,424
during self-defense class.

491
00:36:35,493 --> 00:36:38,951
- You're the new patrol special, aren't you?
- Yeah.

492
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:43,490
<i>Word to the wise, kid.</i>
<i>Your brother was a good man.</i>
<i>Don't cock up his memory.</i>

493
00:36:47,071 --> 00:36:49,164
Let's check
the damage inside.

494
00:36:54,078 --> 00:36:56,069
George.

495
00:36:57,682 --> 00:36:59,707
I'm sorry
about your brother.

496
00:37:08,759 --> 00:37:10,750
Hey.

497
00:37:12,330 --> 00:37:15,265
I bet you I know where
this Kane guy lives.

498
00:37:21,606 --> 00:37:24,166
<i>[Ted]</i>
<i>Is that him?</i>
<i>[George] Yeah.</i>

499
00:37:24,242 --> 00:37:28,269
Good. Now we know he's home.
Let's get outta here.
Come on.

500
00:37:28,346 --> 00:37:31,440
<i>He's up there with his gang.</i>
<i>Five more minutes.</i>
<i>Now.!</i>

501
00:37:31,515 --> 00:37:33,506
[Honking]

502
00:37:33,584 --> 00:37:35,575
Wait one second.

503
00:37:39,290 --> 00:37:41,281
[Laughing]

504
00:37:42,893 --> 00:37:45,987
- Huh.
- You were right.

505
00:37:46,063 --> 00:37:49,191
<i>He was up there</i>
<i>with his gang.</i>
[Chattering]

506
00:37:49,267 --> 00:37:51,701
<i>I think you saw someone else</i>
<i>in the green station wagon.</i>

507
00:37:51,769 --> 00:37:55,535
What could they possibly see
in a man that dresses that badly?

508
00:37:55,606 --> 00:37:59,406
<i>They have to be his alibi.</i>
<i>That's the only explanation.</i>

509
00:38:04,515 --> 00:38:06,813
[Car Alarm Beeps]

510
00:38:06,884 --> 00:38:08,909
<i>[Ted]</i>
<i>You're not gonna follow him.</i>

511
00:38:08,986 --> 00:38:10,851
I think we should
follow the cab.

512
00:38:44,422 --> 00:38:46,413
[BellJingles]

513
00:38:46,490 --> 00:38:50,051
What do you think he's doing
in a Chinese laundry
this time of night?

514
00:38:50,127 --> 00:38:53,028
You saw his gang.
He needs clean sheets.

515
00:39:01,706 --> 00:39:04,402
Oh, yeah. "Tedster,"
I meant to ask you before.

516
00:39:04,475 --> 00:39:07,467
What, uh... What are you
on probation for, anyway?

517
00:39:09,780 --> 00:39:11,771
Moral turpitude.

518
00:39:11,849 --> 00:39:14,943
[Chuckles]
Moral turpitude?

519
00:39:15,019 --> 00:39:18,216
What'd you do, sleep
with the captain's wife
or something?

520
00:39:18,289 --> 00:39:22,123
No. The chief's.

521
00:39:22,193 --> 00:39:25,924
[Laughing]
That's cool.

522
00:39:25,996 --> 00:39:29,363
I didn't know
she was the chief's wife.

523
00:39:29,433 --> 00:39:31,765
I picked her up in the supermarket,
in the frozen foods.

524
00:39:31,836 --> 00:39:34,202
Hmm.

525
00:39:34,271 --> 00:39:37,763
Is she, uh...
Is she pretty?

526
00:39:39,777 --> 00:39:41,768
She's great.

527
00:39:44,448 --> 00:39:46,973
She's a lot younger
than the chief.

528
00:39:47,051 --> 00:39:49,076
That's great.
Way to go, Tedster.

529
00:39:52,156 --> 00:39:54,147
<i>What the hell</i>
<i>has he got there?</i>

530
00:39:54,225 --> 00:39:56,625
A tube of clothing.
[Scoffs]

531
00:40:04,735 --> 00:40:09,035
You wanted to go to his house.
We did. You wanted
to follow him. We did.

532
00:40:09,106 --> 00:40:11,973
<i>This guy's not happening.</i>
<i>Let's get back to work.</i>

533
00:40:26,924 --> 00:40:31,384
Uh, what was...
What was in that cup?
Coffee.

534
00:40:31,462 --> 00:40:34,295
Yeah. Where'd you get it?

535
00:40:34,365 --> 00:40:38,233
- You gave it to me.
- Right.

536
00:40:39,637 --> 00:40:41,628
[Clearing Throat]

537
00:40:41,705 --> 00:40:45,004
<i>[Harriet] Car one,</i>
<i>this is control. Do you copy?</i>
It's for you.

538
00:40:45,075 --> 00:40:47,441
<i>Car one, this is control.</i>
Answer it.

539
00:40:47,511 --> 00:40:50,776
Go ahead.
<i>Car one, this is control.!</i>

540
00:40:50,848 --> 00:40:55,046
- Hello?
<i>- Car one, we have an emergency</i>
<i>at 342 Kearney.</i>

541
00:40:55,119 --> 00:40:57,110
<i>There's a jumper</i>
<i>on the fifth floor.</i>

542
00:40:57,188 --> 00:41:00,089
<i>George, you're all I've got.</i>
<i>This is a customer call.</i>

543
00:41:00,157 --> 00:41:02,887
<i>Thejumper is on the ledge.</i>

544
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:04,222
Shit, did you
see that?
What?

545
00:41:04,295 --> 00:41:05,853
It's Sam Jones.
Who?

546
00:41:05,930 --> 00:41:07,522
Sam Jones.
Come on!
George!

547
00:41:07,598 --> 00:41:10,328
<i>[Harriet]</i>
<i>George, do you copy?</i>
<i>[Ted] George.! Wait.!</i>

548
00:41:10,401 --> 00:41:12,392
George!

549
00:41:14,939 --> 00:41:18,875
<i>[Woman On P.A.]</i>
<i>Advisory for BARTpassengers.</i>
Who's Sam Jones?

550
00:41:18,943 --> 00:41:22,674
<i>No smoking, eating or drinking</i>
<i>is permitted once you</i>
<i>have entered the gates.</i>

551
00:41:22,746 --> 00:41:26,113
<i>Thank you for keeping</i>
<i>BARTsafe and clean.</i>

552
00:41:27,685 --> 00:41:30,153
Watch out.
There he is.

553
00:41:30,221 --> 00:41:35,591
<i>Next Concord-bound train will arrive</i>
<i>at Montgomery Street in two minutes.</i>

554
00:41:37,928 --> 00:41:42,456
