<i>Montgomery Street in two minutes.</i>

555
00:41:42,533 --> 00:41:45,696
["Smashing Into Wall"
Sound Effect]
[Groaning]

556
00:41:58,215 --> 00:42:02,652
Whoo!
[Mumbling]
Okay.

557
00:42:10,694 --> 00:42:12,924
<i>[Woman On P.A.]</i>
<i>Attention, please.</i>

558
00:42:12,997 --> 00:42:17,934
<i>Will Ms. Wills please contact</i>
<i>the station agent at extension 4123.</i>

559
00:42:18,002 --> 00:42:20,436
<i>[Whistle Sounds]</i>

560
00:42:27,678 --> 00:42:30,112
What the hell you think's
in that tube, huh?

561
00:42:30,180 --> 00:42:33,877
[Groans]
Ted?

562
00:42:33,951 --> 00:42:36,852
<i>Next Concord-bound train</i>
<i>will arrive at MacArthur</i>
<i>in two minutes.</i>

563
00:42:36,921 --> 00:42:38,855
Ted?

564
00:42:38,923 --> 00:42:41,323
[Ted] I'm okay. I'm all right.
<i>[Harriet]</i>
<i>George, are you there?</i>

565
00:42:41,392 --> 00:42:43,383
I'm all right!
Are you sure?

566
00:42:43,460 --> 00:42:46,190
<i>[Harriet]</i>
<i>Where in the hell did you go?</i>
We're on our way.

567
00:42:46,263 --> 00:42:48,629
No. We gotta go to the laundry.
We're going to the jumper.

568
00:42:48,699 --> 00:42:50,963
You need a search warrant
for a Chinese laundry.

569
00:42:51,035 --> 00:42:53,333
Move it.
Move it!

570
00:42:57,508 --> 00:42:59,669
Ay, ay, ay, ay, ay.

571
00:43:02,079 --> 00:43:05,310
I'm all right!
[Engine Starts]

572
00:43:07,885 --> 00:43:10,581
[Stomach Gurgling]

573
00:43:10,654 --> 00:43:12,952
Stop looking at me.

574
00:43:13,023 --> 00:43:16,857
[Groaning]

575
00:43:16,927 --> 00:43:20,488
Stop looking at me.
I'm okay. It's just...

576
00:43:20,564 --> 00:43:22,623
something I ate or stress.

577
00:43:23,834 --> 00:43:25,825
[Stomach Gurgling]

578
00:43:30,207 --> 00:43:33,870
[Snoring]
[Tires Screech]

579
00:43:40,451 --> 00:43:46,321
[Snoring]
[Grunts] Ted. Ted?
Ted? Oh, shit.

580
00:43:46,390 --> 00:43:48,858
Ah! Ted!
Jesus! I'm sorry.

581
00:43:48,926 --> 00:43:51,486
L... I'm sorry about
the coffee, all right?

582
00:43:51,562 --> 00:43:54,554
I didn't know you'd turn
out to be such a nice guy!

583
00:43:54,632 --> 00:43:58,398
[Burps]
Ted, Ted, Ted! Wake up!
Come on, Ted.

584
00:43:58,469 --> 00:44:02,872
I don't know what the hell
to do with a jumper!
Ted. Ted!

585
00:44:02,940 --> 00:44:06,273
<i>Ted, come on.!</i>
<i>Ah, don't snore, Ted.</i>

586
00:44:07,611 --> 00:44:09,841
Come on, Ted.
Wake up, buddy.

587
00:44:09,913 --> 00:44:12,279
I need your help.
Come on!
Come on, come on!

588
00:44:12,349 --> 00:44:15,944
Come on.
Wake up, Ted.
[Snoring]

589
00:44:16,020 --> 00:44:19,183
Ooh. Uh, why don't you
stay with the radio, Ted?

590
00:44:20,591 --> 00:44:24,357
He's gonna stay
with the radio.
You see that?

591
00:44:24,428 --> 00:44:28,159
<i>You see that? I want you</i>
<i>to get that son of a bitch</i>
<i>off my building right now.</i>

592
00:44:28,232 --> 00:44:30,598
Maybe we should wait
for the police?
You are the police!

593
00:44:30,668 --> 00:44:32,659
What the hell you think
I'm paying you for?

594
00:44:32,736 --> 00:44:35,671
He's awfully high up there.
How'd he get up there?

595
00:44:35,739 --> 00:44:38,173
Don't you lock
your building at night?

596
00:44:38,242 --> 00:44:41,871
- Kuffs?
- Maya.

597
00:44:41,945 --> 00:44:44,539
What are you doing here?
I thought you were in Brazil.

598
00:44:44,615 --> 00:44:47,243
- Uh, well, l...
- Where are you going?

599
00:44:47,317 --> 00:44:50,650
You remember Robert?
Hi.

600
00:44:50,721 --> 00:44:52,552
Yeah.

601
00:44:52,623 --> 00:44:55,285
Come on. He's gonna jump.
Come on.

602
00:44:55,359 --> 00:44:57,657
It's bad luck if he jumps.
Come on.

603
00:44:57,728 --> 00:44:59,958
<i>Wait a minute.</i>
<i>Are you a cop now?</i>

604
00:45:00,030 --> 00:45:04,091
I'll talk to you in a second.
What the hell took you so long?
I've been waitin' all night.

605
00:45:05,202 --> 00:45:07,432
Okay. Now, he's down here.

606
00:45:07,504 --> 00:45:10,302
Did you see that?
Maya with Robert?

607
00:45:10,374 --> 00:45:13,070
I don't get it.
She left him for me.
Come on, come on.

608
00:45:13,143 --> 00:45:17,307
Maybe they're just friends.
Then again, maybe they're not.

609
00:45:17,381 --> 00:45:20,077
You think he's
better looking than I am?
Come on!

610
00:45:21,485 --> 00:45:24,511
Okay. He's out there.
Now go ahead and do your stuff.

611
00:45:24,588 --> 00:45:26,579
Go ahead.

612
00:45:32,162 --> 00:45:35,461
Howdy.

613
00:45:35,532 --> 00:45:39,798
Pretty nice view
you have here.

614
00:45:39,870 --> 00:45:43,101
Would you... Would you mind
coming on back inside here, please?

615
00:45:46,043 --> 00:45:47,476
Please?

616
00:45:51,014 --> 00:45:53,312
He doesn't want
to come in.
What do you mean?

617
00:45:53,383 --> 00:45:55,374
Look, this is my first
day on the job.

618
00:45:55,452 --> 00:45:57,613
I have no idea what to say
to a potential suicide.

619
00:45:57,688 --> 00:46:00,020
It's simple, sonny.
You want to keep your business?

620
00:46:00,090 --> 00:46:04,356
You get him in here,
or you don't get paid.

621
00:46:04,428 --> 00:46:07,488
I see.
Go ahead.

622
00:46:09,433 --> 00:46:12,300
Hey, asshole!

623
00:46:12,369 --> 00:46:15,202
Yes, you. Look, if you're
gonna jump, jump.

624
00:46:15,272 --> 00:46:17,570
<i>Otherwise, use the bridge</i>
<i>like everybody else.</i>

625
00:46:17,641 --> 00:46:20,735
- You're screwing up traffic down there.
- Say what? Are you crazy?

626
00:46:20,811 --> 00:46:22,836
- How'd I do?
<i>- What do you mean?</i>

627
00:46:22,913 --> 00:46:25,677
<i>- That's all I could think of.</i>
- What do you mean that's
all you could think of?

628
00:46:25,749 --> 00:46:28,513
- It's the best I can do.
<i>- You gotta do better than that.</i>

629
00:46:28,585 --> 00:46:30,519
Ooh! Ooh!
He's coming in.

630
00:46:30,587 --> 00:46:33,522
- He's coming in!
- Is he?

631
00:46:33,590 --> 00:46:35,956
- I'll be a son of a bitch. It worked.
<i>- Of course it worked.</i>

632
00:46:36,026 --> 00:46:38,927
<i>[George]</i>
<i>Let's stand back and give</i>
<i>the guy some room here.</i>

633
00:46:38,996 --> 00:46:41,931
I knew it was gonna work.
I'm a professional.
Let's get him a chair.

634
00:46:46,003 --> 00:46:48,028
- You! Cop!
- Hey.

635
00:46:48,105 --> 00:46:50,096
Die!

636
00:47:14,665 --> 00:47:16,656
Maya Carlton?
Yeah.

637
00:47:28,846 --> 00:47:31,212
Hi.
Hi.

638
00:47:34,451 --> 00:47:36,681
I just came to see
if you were all right.

639
00:47:38,088 --> 00:47:41,751
I've really got to go.
Wait a second.

640
00:47:41,825 --> 00:47:45,886
Um, I want to apologize
to you...

641
00:47:45,963 --> 00:47:47,954
about my note.

642
00:47:49,199 --> 00:47:54,068
That was...
That was not good.
No, it wasn't.

643
00:47:56,406 --> 00:48:01,070
You, uh,
you look amazing.

644
00:48:03,046 --> 00:48:06,140
You know, when I saw you
coming down on that stretcher,

645
00:48:06,216 --> 00:48:09,743
l... I almost died.

646
00:48:20,330 --> 00:48:21,957
Mmm.

647
00:48:22,032 --> 00:48:24,523
Was that you
on the phone?

648
00:48:24,601 --> 00:48:27,536
Yeah. Yeah,
that was me.

649
00:48:29,373 --> 00:48:34,538
George! George, come on!
You're getting a hard-on.

650
00:48:34,611 --> 00:48:36,977
I can't help it. It's you.

651
00:48:37,047 --> 00:48:41,541
- No, it's you.
- Yeah.

652
00:48:41,618 --> 00:48:45,384
Uh, look, what are you doing
with this Robbie character?

653
00:48:45,455 --> 00:48:48,856
Kuffs, come on.
You left me.

654
00:48:48,926 --> 00:48:50,917
Yeah, right.

655
00:48:53,297 --> 00:48:57,734
Does he, uh...
Does he know about the child?

656
00:48:57,801 --> 00:49:03,000
You know, I don't need Robert
and I don't need you.

657
00:49:06,443 --> 00:49:10,038
I've got to go.
I just wanted to see
if you were all right.

658
00:49:11,748 --> 00:49:13,739
Take care of yourself.

659
00:49:29,266 --> 00:49:31,257
Women.

660
00:49:34,671 --> 00:49:38,368
Well, Capt. Morino wouldn't
give me the search warrant
for the laundry.

661
00:49:39,910 --> 00:49:44,813
Ted got suspended.
He doesn't know that yet.
He's still asleep.

662
00:49:44,881 --> 00:49:47,145
I don't know, maybe it's just
the post-gunshot blues,

663
00:49:47,217 --> 00:49:51,517
but I'm beginning to feel like
I'm not exactly cut out for
this line of work, you know?

664
00:49:53,090 --> 00:49:55,456
[Sighs]

665
00:49:55,525 --> 00:49:59,757
Want to see what a gunshot
wound looks like?
[Groaning]

666
00:49:59,830 --> 00:50:03,027
