on guns has changed.

667
00:50:03,100 --> 00:50:06,263
Do cause
quite a bit of pain.

668
00:50:06,336 --> 00:50:08,531
<i>[Dog Barking]</i>
See, the, uh, bullet
went in here...

669
00:50:08,605 --> 00:50:10,869
and then it came out the back.

670
00:50:12,376 --> 00:50:15,436
You feel it hit, and then
there's this, uh,

671
00:50:15,512 --> 00:50:18,572
this kind of a sharp pain.

672
00:50:18,648 --> 00:50:22,243
And then it goes numb.
Yeah.

673
00:50:22,319 --> 00:50:24,310
Scarier than shit.

674
00:50:26,123 --> 00:50:30,457
Now, the guy who jumped,
he was a, uh, a writer.

675
00:50:30,527 --> 00:50:35,521
Ooh! Tried to kill himself
twice before.

676
00:50:35,599 --> 00:50:38,227
[Sighing]
I don't know.

677
00:50:38,301 --> 00:50:43,204
I know Kane killed my brother.
I know Sam Jones is in it with him.

678
00:50:44,307 --> 00:50:46,298
What the hell can I do about it?

679
00:50:48,211 --> 00:50:50,611
I don't have any money.

680
00:50:50,680 --> 00:50:53,148
In two weeks, I'm probably
gonna lose the business
anyway.

681
00:50:53,216 --> 00:50:56,413
There's this $50,000
balloon payment due
on change of ownership...

682
00:50:56,486 --> 00:50:59,580
that Capt. Morino
hasn't spotted yet.

683
00:50:59,656 --> 00:51:02,648
That's it, that's it.
I'm doomed.

684
00:51:17,274 --> 00:51:20,266
If you're not the cleaning lady,
you're in the wrong apartment.

685
00:51:20,343 --> 00:51:24,541
[Laughing]
I've come to make peace,
Mr. Kuffs.

686
00:51:26,483 --> 00:51:29,179
<i>I'm sorry you think</i>
<i>I killed your brother.</i>

687
00:51:29,252 --> 00:51:34,519
I didn't, but I do represent
certain business interests
in your district.

688
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:40,821
There's a $25,000
down payment for your services.

689
00:51:40,897 --> 00:51:43,889
Most of the time,
all we'll ask you to do
is look the other way.

690
00:51:43,967 --> 00:51:47,403
You took your brother's job,
Mr. Kuffs.

691
00:51:47,471 --> 00:51:49,462
You could have a future here.

692
00:51:51,108 --> 00:51:53,042
Then again,
you might not.

693
00:51:57,747 --> 00:51:59,374
[Whistles]

694
00:52:01,551 --> 00:52:06,045
[Sighing]
I think I like having a future.

695
00:52:08,859 --> 00:52:10,850
Thank you, Lee.

696
00:52:22,639 --> 00:52:25,767
Aah!
We're gonna die, Sam!

697
00:52:25,842 --> 00:52:28,709
Oh, I scared you,
didn't I? [Cackles]

698
00:52:28,778 --> 00:52:30,712
You're in big trouble, kid.

699
00:52:30,780 --> 00:52:34,739
Sam, I gotta tell ya.
I was pretty set to quit
the business this morning.

700
00:52:34,818 --> 00:52:37,343
Then your little buddy, Kane,
dropped by, offered me a bribe...

701
00:52:37,420 --> 00:52:41,618
$25,000 to look the other way
while you tear up my district.

702
00:52:41,691 --> 00:52:45,525
I asked for 50,000.
We settled on 37,500.
I think I did pretty good.

703
00:52:45,595 --> 00:52:48,962
Capt. Morino, please.
It's Sam Jones.
It's an emergency.

704
00:52:49,032 --> 00:52:51,500
Police? I'd better
talk fast, huh?

705
00:52:51,568 --> 00:52:54,560
You're into a
land-grab scam, Sam.

706
00:52:54,638 --> 00:52:56,629
Now, the problem is,
you're greedy!

707
00:52:56,706 --> 00:52:59,641
You don't want to pay
top dollar, and people don't
actually want to sell to you.

708
00:52:59,709 --> 00:53:02,701
So you use Kane and his hoods
to come in, shake everybody up...

709
00:53:02,779 --> 00:53:07,148
and then you come in like
a savior with bags of money
and buy everything up!

710
00:53:07,217 --> 00:53:09,310
See, I did a little
research on you.

711
00:53:09,386 --> 00:53:11,479
You're a big shot
art collector,

712
00:53:11,555 --> 00:53:13,819
a major player
on the charity circuit.

713
00:53:13,890 --> 00:53:16,381
You're rich, so you think
you're above the law.

714
00:53:16,459 --> 00:53:18,552
But you've made
two mistakes now, Sam.

715
00:53:18,628 --> 00:53:20,687
Number one, you had Kane
kill my brother.

716
00:53:20,764 --> 00:53:24,928
Number two, the land
you're grabbing happens
to be in my district.

717
00:53:25,001 --> 00:53:28,437
And in my district, Sambo,
I am the law.

718
00:53:28,505 --> 00:53:31,235
Capt. Morino, one of your
patrol specials...

719
00:53:31,308 --> 00:53:34,243
just broke into my car
and is threatening me.

720
00:53:34,311 --> 00:53:38,304
George Kuffs.
He wants to talk to you.

721
00:53:38,381 --> 00:53:40,815
[Morino, Indistinct]
Naw,
I don't think so.

722
00:53:40,884 --> 00:53:45,878
<i>[Hangs Up Receiver]</i>
It's just you and me, Sam.
No corroborating witnesses.

723
00:53:45,956 --> 00:53:49,949
Your word against mine.
Pull over right here, huh?
I'll walk the rest of the way.

724
00:53:53,196 --> 00:53:56,097
I wish there were something
I could say, Mr. Kuffs,

725
00:53:56,166 --> 00:53:58,361
to make you feel better
about yourself.

726
00:53:58,435 --> 00:54:00,926
[Sighs]

727
00:54:01,004 --> 00:54:04,804
I guess you could tell me
you're gonna leave town
for 200 or 300 years.

728
00:54:04,874 --> 00:54:06,865
That'd make me feel
a little better.

729
00:54:08,345 --> 00:54:10,836
Thank you.

730
00:54:15,885 --> 00:54:18,854
Oh, God,
that felt good!

731
00:54:20,991 --> 00:54:25,621
I almost told him I knew about
him and Kane and the laundry.

732
00:54:25,695 --> 00:54:27,629
What if there were drugs
in that tube or something?

733
00:54:27,697 --> 00:54:32,532
What he doesn't know I know
can hurt him, so why the hell
should I tell him, huh?

734
00:54:32,602 --> 00:54:36,595
Yeah, you see,
this way I can stake him
and Kane out with my team.

735
00:54:36,673 --> 00:54:38,732
I can catch them both
red-handed!

736
00:54:38,808 --> 00:54:40,969
I like it.
It sounds good.

737
00:54:41,044 --> 00:54:42,807
[Chattering]

738
00:54:42,879 --> 00:54:45,006
[Jingles]

739
00:54:45,081 --> 00:54:48,847
Guess what I have in the bag?
Capt. Morino wants you
to call him right away.

740
00:54:51,054 --> 00:54:54,581
He sounded
really pissed off.
Yeah, in a minute.

741
00:54:54,658 --> 00:54:56,592
Hey, guys,
what's going on?

742
00:54:56,660 --> 00:54:58,753
Nothing personal, George,

743
00:54:58,828 --> 00:55:00,989
but we all decided we don't
want you as our boss.

744
00:55:01,064 --> 00:55:03,624
[Scoffs]
Well, this is a first.

745
00:55:03,700 --> 00:55:06,965
A boss being fired by
his own employees.

746
00:55:07,037 --> 00:55:10,097
Tell me, Bill, who do you think
should be boss, my little friend?

747
00:55:10,173 --> 00:55:12,164
Me.

748
00:55:12,242 --> 00:55:16,076
Nothing personal, Bill,
but, uh, you're fired.

749
00:55:16,146 --> 00:55:18,876
You can't fire me.
These people want me.

750
00:55:18,948 --> 00:55:22,179
<i>We're not saying you can't own</i>
<i>the business, we're saying...</i>

751
00:55:22,252 --> 00:55:25,016
find somebody else
with experience to run it!

752
00:55:25,088 --> 00:55:27,784
Is that what
you're saying?
<i>That's right.</i>

753
00:55:27,857 --> 00:55:31,315
Well, listen.
Since I have taken this job,
I've been shouted at,

754
00:55:31,394 --> 00:55:33,521
I've been bribed,
I've even been shot
for you people!

755
00:55:33,596 --> 00:55:37,760
And now you're telling me
you don't believe in me?
This is what we're gonna do.

756
00:55:37,834 --> 00:55:40,632
If Bill beats me in
a fair fight right here, right now,

757
00:55:40,704 --> 00:55:43,468
<i>not only can Bill be boss...</i>

758
00:55:43,540 --> 00:55:45,474
I'll give you the business for free.

759
00:55:45,542 --> 00:55:47,305
- What do you say?
- You're not serious?

760
00:55:47,377 --> 00:55:51,746
Yeah, I am.
But I gotta warn you,
I'm pretty good.

761
00:55:51,815 --> 00:55:56,218
<i>So if I win, I'm boss.</i>

762
00:55:56,286 --> 00:55:59,813
<i>If I sayjump, your only answer</i>
<i>is "how high. '"</i>

763
00:55:59,889 --> 00:56:02,881
You're on.
Come on, Bill.

764
00:56:02,959 --> 00:56:07,123
He was Golden Glove champion
twice, George. Forget it.

765
00:56:07,197 --> 00:56:09,563
Hey, a deal's a deal.
You can't back out now.

766
00:56:09,632 --> 00:56:12,624
All right, just
make it quick, Bill.

767
00:56:12,702 --> 00:56:15,330
- You won't feel a thing.
- Thank you.

768
00:56:15,405 --> 00:56:18,772
Ooh!
[Gasping]

769
00:56:22,679 --> 00:56:25,079
I win!

770
00:56:27,117 --> 00:56:29,847
Why didn't I think of that
last night with Ted?

771
00:56:31,721 --> 00:56:35,817
Okay, that'll be $113.65.

772
00:56:35,892 --> 00:56:39,020
All right.
What would you like
the card to say?

773
00:56:39,095 --> 00:56:41,029
Ah, "Dear Maya,

774
00:56:41,097 --> 00:56:44,396
"it was great seeing you
the other night.

775
00:56:44,467 --> 00:56:48,665
Love and kisses on
all your pink parts. George."

776
00:56:48,738 --> 00:56:51,764
I guess you hear that
all the time, don't you?
[Harriet] Come in, George.

777
00:56:51,841 --> 00:56:54,435
Excuse me.

778
00:56:56,012 --> 00:56:57,946
Yeah, come in. Ten-four.

779
00:56:58,014 --> 00:57:00,881
[Harriet, Loud]
I got Bill on the line, and
Morino's called twice more.

780
00:57:00,950 --> 00:57:04,010
You better call him soon.
Now, here's Bill.

781
00:57:04,087 --> 00:57:08,888
Just checkin' in, boss. Sam Jones
got home 15 minutes ago.

782
00:57:11,094 --> 00:57:13,028
[In High Voice]
Hasn't moved since.

783
00:57:13,096 --> 00:57:17,123
All right. Why don't
you just call me back
in about a half hour?

784
00:57:18,301 --> 00:57:21,759
May I ask you
a personal question?
Sure.

785
00:57:21,838 --> 00:57:24,033
Have you ever, uh,
been married?

786
00:57:24,107 --> 00:57:26,200
[Chuckles]
Goin' on 18 years.

787
00:57:26,276 --> 00:57:30,303
Eighteen years.
Geez!

788
00:57:30,380 --> 00:57:32,507
What's it like?

789
00:57:32,582 --> 00:57:34,880
Is it still fun?
You still like her?

790
00:57:34,951 --> 00:57:37,249
- Him.
- Oh.

791
00:57:37,320 --> 00:57:41,586
Yeah, it's great. It has
its ups and downs, but it's great.

792
00:57:43,960 --> 00:57:46,724
- Thank you.
- Sure.

793
00:57:47,797 --> 00:57:50,994
<i>Have a nice day.</i>
You too.

794
00:57:51,067 --> 00:57:53,001
When do you think
she'll get these?

795
00:57:53,069 --> 00:57:56,869
Well, I'll call Sacramento right away.
Say, by 2:00?

796
00:57:56,940 --> 00:57:58,999
[Beeping]
[Nikki On Radio]
George, are you there?

797
00:57:59,075 --> 00:58:01,066
I think I want to
change the card.

798
00:58:01,144 --> 00:58:04,113
Yeah, come in.
I lost Kane.

799
00:58:04,180 --> 00:58:08,014
He turned a corner
and I turned the corner,
and he just wasn't there.

800
00:58:08,084 --> 00:58:11,542
I'm sorry, George.
I'm not very good at this.

801
00:58:11,621 --> 00:58:14,590
That's quite all right, Nikki.
I have a good idea where he's going.

802
00:58:14,657 --> 00:58:18,616
Why don't you go hang out
by the laundry or something?

803
00:58:19,863 --> 00:58:24,095
Hey, wait! Weren't you
gonna change the card?

804
00:58:24,167 --> 00:58:26,567
Right, right.

805
00:58:26,636 --> 00:58:28,763
"Dear Maya,
I really, really miss you.

806
00:58:28,838 --> 00:58:31,534
"Would love it if you
came to San Francisco
tonight for dinner.

807
00:58:31,608 --> 00:58:34,736
But even if you can't,
I'd still love to talk
to you. Love, George."

808
00:58:34,811 --> 00:58:36,938
Better.
Much better.

809
00:58:37,013 --> 00:58:39,538
Yeah, I think so.

810
00:58:48,525 --> 00:58:51,961
I am not interested
in selling at any price!

811
00:58:52,028 --> 00:58:53,962
<i>I understand</i>
<i>your store was robbed.</i>
<i>Yes.</i>

812
00:58:54,030 --> 00:58:55,964
Well, well, well.
Kane.

813
00:58:56,032 --> 00:58:57,966
I should know you'd be
standing right next
to the toilet paper.

814
00:58:58,034 --> 00:59:01,060
What are you doing here?
I fired you!

815
00:59:01,137 --> 00:59:05,870
I know you fired me,
but you paid up through
next week, so here I am.

816
00:59:05,942 --> 00:59:08,172
May I speak to you
for a moment, please?

817
00:59:09,512 --> 00:59:11,412
Come on, come on!

818
00:59:15,018 --> 00:59:17,851
Look, before we
get into this,

819
00:59:17,921 --> 00:59:20,116
there's something I've
been meaning to ask you.

820
00:59:20,189 --> 00:59:23,090
It's been bothering me
for quite some time now.

821
00:59:23,159 --> 00:59:26,253
Where do you buy
your clothing?

822
00:59:26,329 --> 00:59:29,924
What are you doing?
What am I doing?
My job.

823
00:59:29,999 --> 00:59:33,435
See, I just overheard
you asking Mr. Chang
to sell his business.

824
00:59:33,503 --> 00:59:35,801
He said he didn't want to,
but you persisted.

825
00:59:35,872 --> 00:59:38,773
So as much as I like you,
Kane, I'm gonna have
to ask you to leave.

826
00:59:38,841 --> 00:59:42,538
We had a deal, kid.
I paid you this morning.
Absolutely.

827
00:59:42,612 --> 00:59:46,241
You hired me to protect
your interests, and I
fully intend to do that.

828
00:59:46,316 --> 00:59:48,580
You see,
I also have a deal
with Mr. Chang.

829
00:59:48,651 --> 00:59:51,779
And right now, you're on
his property. That's why
I have to ask you to leave.

830
00:59:51,854 --> 00:59:54,379
Don't mess with me, kid.

831
00:59:54,457 --> 00:59:56,823
You see, if Mr. Chang
were on your property...

832
00:59:56,893 --> 00:59:59,726
and he was leaning on you,
I'd ask him to leave.

833
00:59:59,796 --> 01:00:01,787
And then, if he didn't
do it fast enough,

834
01:00:01,864 --> 01:00:03,923
I'd pull my gun
out of its holster
just like this...

835
01:00:04,000 --> 01:00:06,298
and I would shout,
"Do we have
an understanding...

836
01:00:06,369 --> 01:00:09,429
or do you want to see
if you can breathe
through your forehead?"

837
01:00:09,505 --> 01:00:13,168
But I don't have to do that
with you, Kane, because
we're pals, aren't we?

838
01:00:14,243 --> 01:00:16,473
You might not live
to regret this.

839
01:00:16,546 --> 01:00:19,379
I've lived to regret almost
everything I've done.
See ya.

840
01:00:22,485 --> 01:00:25,579
You are going to
get us all killed.

841
01:00:25,655 --> 01:00:28,590
I hope not.

842
01:00:28,658 --> 01:00:32,059
Think positive, Mr. Chang.
Maybe we'll get lucky and win.

843
01:00:38,801 --> 01:00:43,329
[Line Ringing]
[Sighs]

844
01:00:47,176 --> 01:00:50,202
He said he was going home.
But if he's there, he's
not answering his phone.

845
01:00:50,279 --> 01:00:54,306
Try him again.

846
01:00:57,720 --> 01:01:00,621
<i>[Phone Ringing]</i>

847
01:01:05,228 --> 01:01:08,254
<i>[Shower Running]</i>

848
01:01:15,038 --> 01:01:17,097
Hey! Well, Maya's
coming to dinner.

849
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:19,573
I guess the flowers
worked, huh?

850
01:01:19,642 --> 01:01:22,475
Now get out
of my bathroom.

851
01:01:23,446 --> 01:01:25,437
[Phone Ringing]

852
01:01:28,051 --> 01:01:31,646
- Where's he stayin'?
- Brad's apartment.

853
01:01:31,721 --> 01:01:34,588
If the son of a bitch calls in,
you tell him to meet me there...

854
01:01:34,657 --> 01:01:37,683
and to cease and desist
all operations.
You tell him.

855
01:01:37,760 --> 01:01:41,059
You tell him there's
a $50,000 balloon payment due
on the change of ownership...

856
01:01:41,130 --> 01:01:45,396
and that his banker, Mr. Alan
Eddy, wants it today or he's
no longer a patrol special.

857
01:01:45,468 --> 01:01:48,665
What you're doing
is shitty!

858
01:01:48,738 --> 01:01:50,865
<i>Dancin'</i>

859
01:01:50,940 --> 01:01:53,602
<i>Like the floor's</i>
<i>on fire</i>

860
01:01:53,676 --> 01:01:57,669
<i>And we're never</i>
<i>touching the ground</i>

861
01:01:57,747 --> 01:02:00,238
<i>Well, she lifts me</i>

862
01:02:00,316 --> 01:02:02,682
<i>A little bit higher</i>

863
01:02:02,752 --> 01:02:06,711
<i>And our love</i>
<i>Well, there's no comin'down</i>

864
01:02:07,757 --> 01:02:09,452
<i>She'll be runnin'red hot</i>

865
01:02:09,525 --> 01:02:11,516
<i>I can't put out the flame</i>

866
01:02:12,695 --> 01:02:16,187
<i>She tears me up</i>
<i>like a hurricane</i>

867
01:02:17,533 --> 01:02:20,297
<i>She's a roller coaster</i>
<i>She's a tidal wave</i>

868
01:02:22,305 --> 01:02:24,239
<i>She takes my breath</i>
<i>away</i>

869
01:02:24,307 --> 01:02:26,832
<i>Oh, she takes</i>
<i>takes my breath</i>

870
01:02:26,909 --> 01:02:32,677
<i>Takes my breath every time</i>
<i>she moves that way</i>

871
01:02:34,016 --> 01:02:36,109
<i>All my words</i>

872
01:02:36,185 --> 01:02:38,585
<i>Hard to say</i>

873
01:02:38,654 --> 01:02:43,250
<i>Oh, she takes</i>
<i>my breath away</i>

874
01:02:44,360 --> 01:02:48,626
<i>Watch out</i>
<i>She's like dynamite</i>

875
01:02:48,698 --> 01:02:52,964
<i>And she could go off</i>
<i>anytime</i>
Perfect.

876
01:02:53,035 --> 01:02:56,596
<i>Fascination</i>
<i>stimulation</i>

877
01:02:56,672 --> 01:02:58,663
What do you think?
Too subtle?

878
01:02:58,741 --> 01:03:03,405
<i>Now she's got me</i>
<i>so hypnotized</i>
[Sighs]

879
01:03:03,479 --> 01:03:06,915
<i>She takes my breath away</i>

880
01:03:06,983 --> 01:03:09,178
<i>Hey, hey, hey</i>

881
01:03:12,388 --> 01:03:15,380
<i>[Buzzing]</i>

882
01:03:19,695 --> 01:03:21,686
Show time!

883
01:03:25,234 --> 01:03:27,293
Well, she's early.

884
01:03:27,370 --> 01:03:29,531
It's a good sign.

885
01:03:29,605 --> 01:03:31,732
I know it's tacky to
answer the door half-dressed,

